      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think it\u0027s possible to leak a socket here because `initnatpmp` can return an error after it has opened its socket (`NATPMP_ERR_FCNTLERROR`, `NATPMP_ERR_CANNOTGETGATEWAY`, `NATPMP_ERR_CONNECTERR`). To prevent this, we\u0027d need to either check the error code and manually call `closenatpmp` if needed, or patch libnatpmp so that it automatically closes the socket in these cases.",
      "range": {
