      "writtenOn": "2026-05-26T20:27:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 137: closeNatPmpHandle() reads/writes natpmpHdlInitialized_ and natpmpHdl_ without consistently holding natpmpMutex_. It is called from the destructor, initNatPmp(), terminate(), and clearIgds(), while NAT-PMP operations may also use the handle, which can produce a data race or close the handle while another operation is using it. Make handle lifetime changes consistently protected by natpmpMutex_ or require callers to hold the mutex and assert/document that contract.\n```suggestion\nvoid\nNatPmp::closeNatPmpHandle()\n{\n    std::lock_guard lock(natpmpMutex_);\n    if (!natpmpHdlInitialized_)\n        return;\n\n    auto err \u003d closenatpmp(\u0026natpmpHdl_);\n    if (err \u003c 0 and logger_)\n        logger_-\u003ewarn(\"NAT-PMP: Failed to close libnatpmp handle: {}\", getNatPmpErrorStr(err));\n    memset(\u0026natpmpHdl_, 0, sizeof(natpmpHdl_));\n    natpmpHdlInitialized_ \u003d false;\n}\n```",
      "revId": "46b42818adf5cdaf05749ca4274847396f9f845e",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
    },
