      "writtenOn": "2026-05-26T20:27:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 262: releaseProtocolResources is derived only from controllerList_.empty(), so shutdown with an empty controller list will also deinitialize protocol resources here despite the comment saying terminate() owns shutdown cleanup. That makes shutdown cleanup order dependent and can race with pending protocol operations that terminate() is meant to drain/detach first. Gate this on !shuttingDown so resource release only happens for the regular last-controller stop path.\n```suggestion\nauto releaseProtocolResources \u003d !shuttingDown \u0026\u0026 controllerList_.empty();\n```",
